question: Find the id and color description of the products with at least 2 characteristics.
query: SELECT T1.PRODUCT_ID, T2.COLOR_DESCRIPTION FROM PRODUCTS_GEN_CHARACTERISTICS_PRODUCTS T1 JOIN PRODUCTS_GEN_CHARACTERISTICS_REF_COLORS T2 ON T1.COLOR_CODE = T2.COLOR_CODE JOIN PRODUCTS_GEN_CHARACTERISTICS_PRODUCT_CHARACTERISTICS T3 ON T1.PRODUCT_ID = T3.PRODUCT_ID GROUP BY T1.PRODUCT_ID, T2.COLOR_DESCRIPTION HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2

question: In which year were most departments established?

question: Show the name and number of employees for the departments managed by heads whose temporary acting value is 'Yes'?
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  T1.NUM_EMPLOYEES FROM DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_DEPARTMENT T1 JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_MANAGEMENT T2 ON T1.DEPARTMENT_ID  =  T2.DEPARTMENT_ID WHERE T2.TEMPORARY_ACTING  =  'Yes'

question: How many departments are led by heads who are not mentioned?

question: What are the distinct ages of the heads who are acting?
query: SELECT DISTINCT T1.AGE FROM DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_MANAGEMENT T2 JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_HEAD T1 ON T1.HEAD_ID  =  T2.HEAD_ID WHERE T2.TEMPORARY_ACTING  =  'Yes'

question: List the states where both the secretary of 'Treasury' department and the secretary of 'Homeland Security' were born.
query: SELECT T3.BORN_STATE FROM DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_DEPARTMENT T1 JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_MANAGEMENT T2 ON T1.DEPARTMENT_ID  =  T2.DEPARTMENT_ID JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_HEAD T3 ON T2.HEAD_ID  =  T3.HEAD_ID WHERE T1.NAME  =  'Treasury' INTERSECT SELECT T3.BORN_STATE FROM DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_DEPARTMENT T1 JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_MANAGEMENT T2 ON T1.DEPARTMENT_ID  =  T2.DEPARTMENT_ID JOIN DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_HEAD T3 ON T2.HEAD_ID  =  T3.HEAD_ID WHERE T1.NAME  =  'Homeland Security'

question: Which department has more than 1 head at a time? List the id, name and the number of heads.

question: Which head's name has the substring 'Ha'? List the id and name.
query: SELECT HEAD_ID ,  NAME FROM DEPARTMENT_MANAGEMENT_HEAD WHERE UPPER(NAME) LIKE UPPER('%Ha%')

question: Find the first names and offices of all instructors who have taught some course and also find the course description.
query: SELECT T2.EMP_FNAME ,  T4.PROF_OFFICE ,  T3.CRS_DESCRIPTION FROM COLLEGE_1_CLASS T1 JOIN COLLEGE_1_EMPLOYEE T2 ON T1.PROF_NUM  =  T2.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_COURSE T3 ON T1.CRS_CODE  =  T3.CRS_CODE JOIN COLLEGE_1_PROFESSOR T4 ON T2.EMP_NUM  =  T4.EMP_NUM

question: What are the first names, office locations of all lecturers who have taught some course?
query: SELECT T2.EMP_FNAME ,  T4.PROF_OFFICE ,  T3.CRS_DESCRIPTION FROM COLLEGE_1_CLASS T1 JOIN COLLEGE_1_EMPLOYEE T2 ON T1.PROF_NUM  =  T2.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_COURSE T3 ON T1.CRS_CODE  =  T3.CRS_CODE JOIN COLLEGE_1_PROFESSOR T4 ON T2.EMP_NUM  =  T4.EMP_NUM

question: Find the first names and offices of all instructors who have taught some course and the course description and the department name.
query: SELECT T2.EMP_FNAME ,  T4.PROF_OFFICE ,  T3.CRS_DESCRIPTION ,  T5.DEPT_NAME FROM COLLEGE_1_CLASS T1 JOIN COLLEGE_1_EMPLOYEE T2 ON T1.PROF_NUM  =  T2.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_COURSE T3 ON T1.CRS_CODE  =  T3.CRS_CODE JOIN COLLEGE_1_PROFESSOR T4 ON T2.EMP_NUM  =  T4.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_DEPARTMENT T5 ON T4.DEPT_CODE  =  T5.DEPT_CODE

question: What are the first names, office locations, and departments of all instructors, and also what are the descriptions of the courses they teach?
query: SELECT T2.EMP_FNAME ,  T4.PROF_OFFICE ,  T3.CRS_DESCRIPTION ,  T5.DEPT_NAME FROM COLLEGE_1_CLASS T1 JOIN COLLEGE_1_EMPLOYEE T2 ON T1.PROF_NUM  =  T2.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_COURSE T3 ON T1.CRS_CODE  =  T3.CRS_CODE JOIN COLLEGE_1_PROFESSOR T4 ON T2.EMP_NUM  =  T4.EMP_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_DEPARTMENT T5 ON T4.DEPT_CODE  =  T5.DEPT_CODE

question: Find names of all students who took some course and the course description.
query: SELECT T1.STU_FNAME ,  T1.STU_LNAME ,  T4.CRS_DESCRIPTION FROM COLLEGE_1_STUDENT T1 JOIN COLLEGE_1_ENROLL T2 ON T1.STU_NUM  =  T2.STU_NUM JOIN COLLEGE_1_CLASS T3 ON T2.CLASS_CODE  =  T3.CLASS_CODE JOIN COLLEGE_1_COURSE T4 ON T3.CRS_CODE  =  T4.CRS_CODE

question: What are the names of all students who took a class and the corresponding course descriptions?

question: Find names of all students who took some course and got A or C.

question: What are the names of all students taking a course who received an A or C?

question: What is the average duration of songs that have mp3 format and resolution below 800?
query: SELECT LPAD(FLOOR(AVG_SECONDS / 60), 2,'0' ) || ':' || LPAD( MOD(AVG_SECONDS, 60), 2, '0' ) AS DURATION FROM ( SELECT AVG(TO_NUMBER(SUBSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, 1, INSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, ':') - 1)) * 60 + TO_NUMBER(SUBSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, INSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, ':') + 1))) AS AVG_SECONDS FROM MUSIC_1_FILES JOIN MUSIC_1_SONG ON MUSIC_1_FILES.F_ID = MUSIC_1_SONG.F_ID WHERE MUSIC_1_FILES.FORMATS = 'mp3' AND MUSIC_1_SONG.RESOLUTION < 800)

question: What is the average song duration for the songs that are in mp3 format and whose resolution below 800?
query: SELECT LPAD(FLOOR(AVG_SECONDS / 60), 2,'0' ) || ':' || LPAD( MOD(AVG_SECONDS, 60), 2, '0' ) AS DURATION FROM ( SELECT AVG(TO_NUMBER(SUBSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, 1, INSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, ':') - 1)) * 60 + TO_NUMBER(SUBSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, INSTR(MUSIC_1_FILES.DURATION, ':') + 1))) AS AVG_SECONDS FROM MUSIC_1_FILES JOIN MUSIC_1_SONG ON MUSIC_1_FILES.F_ID = MUSIC_1_SONG.F_ID WHERE MUSIC_1_FILES.FORMATS = 'mp3' AND MUSIC_1_SONG.RESOLUTION < 800)

question: For each director, return the director's name together with the title of the movie they directed that received the highest rating among all of their movies, and the value of that rating. Ignore movies whose director is NULL.
query: SELECT DIRECTOR, TITLE, STARS FROM (SELECT T2.DIRECTOR AS DIRECTOR, T2.TITLE AS TITLE, T1.STARS, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY T2.DIRECTOR ORDER BY T1.STARS DESC, T2.TITLE) AS RN FROM MOVIE_1_RATING T1 JOIN MOVIE_1_MOVIE T2 ON T1.MID = T2.MID WHERE T2.DIRECTOR IS NOT NULL) WHERE RN = 1 ORDER BY DIRECTOR

question: For each director, what are the titles and ratings for all the movies they reviewed?

question: Find the title and star rating of the movie that got the least rating star for each reviewer.
query: SELECT TITLE, RID, STARS, MIN_STARS FROM (SELECT T2.TITLE AS TITLE, T1.RID, T1.STARS, MIN(T1.STARS) OVER (PARTITION BY T1.RID) AS MIN_STARS, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY T1.RID ORDER BY T1.STARS, T2.TITLE) AS RN FROM MOVIE_1_RATING T1 JOIN MOVIE_1_MOVIE T2 ON T1.MID = T2.MID) WHERE RN = 1

question: For each reviewer id, what is the title and rating for the movie with the smallest rating?

question: Find the title and score of the movie with the lowest rating among all movies directed by each director.
query: SELECT TITLE, MIN_STARS AS STARS, DIRECTOR FROM (SELECT T2.TITLE AS TITLE, T1.STARS, MIN(T1.STARS) OVER (PARTITION BY T2.DIRECTOR) AS MIN_STARS, T2.DIRECTOR AS DIRECTOR, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY T2.DIRECTOR ORDER BY T1.STARS, T2.TITLE) AS RN FROM MOVIE_1_RATING T1 JOIN MOVIE_1_MOVIE T2 ON T1.MID = T2.MID) WHERE RN = 1

question: For each phone, show its names and total number of stocks.

question: Show the names of phones that have total number of stocks bigger than 2000, in descending order of the total number of stocks.

question: What are the id and name of the stadium where the most injury accidents happened?

question: Find the id and name of the stadium where the largest number of injury accidents occurred.

question: In which season and which stadium did any player have an injury of 'Foot injury' or 'Knee problem'?

question: List the name of the stadium where both the player 'Walter Samuel' and the player 'Thiago Motta' got injured.
query: SELECT T2.NAME FROM GAME_INJURY_GAME T1 JOIN GAME_INJURY_STADIUM T2 ON T1.STADIUM_ID  =  T2.ID JOIN GAME_INJURY_INJURY_ACCIDENT T3 ON T1.ID  =  T3.GAME_ID WHERE T3.PLAYER  =  'Walter Samuel' INTERSECT SELECT T2.NAME FROM GAME_INJURY_GAME T1 JOIN GAME_INJURY_STADIUM T2 ON T1.STADIUM_ID  =  T2.ID JOIN GAME_INJURY_INJURY_ACCIDENT T3 ON T1.ID  =  T3.GAME_ID WHERE T3.PLAYER  =  'Thiago Motta'

question: What is the name of the browser that became compatible with the accelerator 'CProxy' after year 1998 ?

question: What is the id and name of the browser that is compatible with the most web accelerators?
query: SELECT T1.ID, T1.NAME FROM BROWSER_WEB_BROWSER T1 JOIN BROWSER_WEB_ACCELERATOR_COMPATIBLE_BROWSER T2 ON T1.ID = T2.BROWSER_ID GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.NAME HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(*)) FROM BROWSER_WEB_BROWSER T3 JOIN BROWSER_WEB_ACCELERATOR_COMPATIBLE_BROWSER T4 ON T3.ID = T4.BROWSER_ID GROUP BY T3.ID)

question: When did the web accelerator 'CACHEbox' and browser 'Internet Explorer' become compatible?

question: Show names for all employees who have certificates on both Boeing 737-800 and Airbus A340-300.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM FLIGHT_1_EMPLOYEE T1 JOIN FLIGHT_1_CERTIFICATE T2 ON T1.EID  =  T2.EID JOIN FLIGHT_1_AIRCRAFT T3 ON T3.AID  =  T2.AID WHERE T3.NAME  =  'Boeing 737-800' INTERSECT SELECT T1.NAME FROM FLIGHT_1_EMPLOYEE T1 JOIN FLIGHT_1_CERTIFICATE T2 ON T1.EID  =  T2.EID JOIN FLIGHT_1_AIRCRAFT T3 ON T3.AID  =  T2.AID WHERE T3.NAME  =  'Airbus A340-300'

question: Show the name of aircraft which fewest people have its certificate.
query: SELECT T2.NAME FROM (SELECT T1.AID FROM FLIGHT_1_CERTIFICATE T1 GROUP BY T1.AID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY) T3 JOIN FLIGHT_1_AIRCRAFT T2 ON T2.AID = T3.AID

question: Show the name and distance of the aircrafts with more than 5000 distance and which at least 5 people have its certificate.

question: what is the salary and name of the employee who has the most number of aircraft certificates?
query: SELECT T1.NAME, T1.SALARY FROM (SELECT T1.NAME, T1.SALARY, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM FLIGHT_1_EMPLOYEE T1 JOIN FLIGHT_1_CERTIFICATE T2 ON T1.EID = T2.EID GROUP BY T1.EID, T1.NAME, T1.SALARY ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) T1 WHERE ROWNUM = 1

question: Find the name and address of the customers who have both New and Pending orders.

question: What are the distinct names of customers who have purchased at least three different products?

question: Show the names of members and the locations of colleges they go to in ascending alphabetical order of member names.

question: Show the distinct leader names of colleges associated with members from country "Canada".
query: SELECT DISTINCT T1.LEADER_NAME FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_COLLEGE T1 JOIN DECORATION_COMPETITION_MEMBER T2 ON T1.COLLEGE_ID  =  T2.COLLEGE_ID WHERE T2.COUNTRY  =  'Canada'

question: Show the names of members and the decoration themes they have.
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  T2.DECORATION_THEME FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_MEMBER T1 JOIN DECORATION_COMPETITION_ROUND T2 ON T1.MEMBER_ID  =  T2.MEMBER_ID

question: Show the names of members that have a rank in round higher than 3.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_MEMBER T1 JOIN DECORATION_COMPETITION_ROUND T2 ON T1.MEMBER_ID  =  T2.MEMBER_ID WHERE T2.RANK_IN_ROUND  >  3

question: Show the names of members in ascending order of their rank in rounds.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_MEMBER T1 JOIN DECORATION_COMPETITION_ROUND T2 ON T1.MEMBER_ID  =  T2.MEMBER_ID ORDER BY RANK_IN_ROUND ASC

question: List the names of members who did not participate in any round.
query: SELECT NAME FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_MEMBER WHERE MEMBER_ID NOT IN (SELECT MEMBER_ID FROM DECORATION_COMPETITION_ROUND)

question: Show the name and phone for customers with a mailshot with outcome code 'No Response'.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME ,  T1.CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_MAILSHOT_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T2.OUTCOME_CODE  =  'No Response'

question: Show the names of customers who have at least 2 mailshots with outcome code 'Order'.
query: SELECT T2.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_MAILSHOT_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.OUTCOME_CODE = 'Order' GROUP BY T2.CUSTOMER_NAME, T1.CUSTOMER_ID HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2

question: Show the names of customers who have the most mailshots.
query: SELECT T2.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM (SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_ID, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_MAILSHOT_CUSTOMERS T1 GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY) T3 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T3.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID

question: What are the name and payment method of customers who have both mailshots in 'Order' outcome and mailshots in 'No Response' outcome.
query: SELECT T2.CUSTOMER_NAME ,  T2.PAYMENT_METHOD FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_MAILSHOT_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.OUTCOME_CODE  =  'Order' INTERSECT SELECT T2.CUSTOMER_NAME ,  T2.PAYMENT_METHOD FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_MAILSHOT_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.OUTCOME_CODE  =  'No Response'

question: Show the premise type and address type code for all customer addresses.

question: What are the distinct address type codes for all customer addresses?
query: SELECT DISTINCT ADDRESS_TYPE_CODE FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMER_ADDRESSES

question: Show the shipping charge and customer id for customer orders with order status Cancelled or Paid.
query: SELECT ORDER_SHIPPING_CHARGES ,  CUSTOMER_ID FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMER_ORDERS WHERE ORDER_STATUS_CODE  =  'Cancelled' OR ORDER_STATUS_CODE  =  'Paid'

question: Show the names of customers having an order with shipping method FedEx and order status Paid.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_CAMPAIGNS_ECOMMERCE_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE SHIPPING_METHOD_CODE  =  'FedEx' AND ORDER_STATUS_CODE  =  'Paid'

question: What are the maximum fastest lap speed in races held after 2004 grouped by race name and ordered by year?

question: For each race name, What is the maximum fastest lap speed for races after 2004 ordered by year?

question: Find the id, forename and number of races of all drivers who have at least participated in two races?

question: What is the id, forename, and number of races for all drivers that have participated in at least 2 races?

question: What are the average fastest lap speed in races held after 2004 grouped by race name and ordered by year?
query: SELECT AVG(CASE WHEN REGEXP_LIKE(T2.FASTESTLAPSPEED, '^[0-9]+(.[0-9]+)?$') THEN TO_NUMBER(T2.FASTESTLAPSPEED) END) AS AVG_SPEED, T1.NAME, MIN(T1.YEAR) AS YEAR FROM FORMULA_1_RACES T1 JOIN FORMULA_1_RESULTS T2 ON T1.RACEID = T2.RACEID WHERE T1.YEAR > 2014 GROUP BY T1.NAME ORDER BY MIN(T1.YEAR)

question: What is the average fastest lap speed for races held after 2004, for each race, ordered by year?
query: SELECT AVG(CASE WHEN REGEXP_LIKE(T2.FASTESTLAPSPEED, '^[0-9]+(.[0-9]+)?$') THEN TO_NUMBER(T2.FASTESTLAPSPEED) END) AS AVG_SPEED, T1.NAME, MIN(T1.YEAR) AS YEAR FROM FORMULA_1_RACES T1 JOIN FORMULA_1_RESULTS T2 ON T1.RACEID = T2.RACEID WHERE T1.YEAR > 2014 GROUP BY T1.NAME ORDER BY MIN(T1.YEAR)

question: What is the average time span of contact channels in the database?
query: SELECT AVG(EXTRACT(DAY FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) + EXTRACT(HOUR FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / 24 + EXTRACT(MINUTE FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / (24 * 60) + EXTRACT(SECOND FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / (24 * 60 * 60)) AS AVG_DAYS FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_ADDRESSES_CUSTOMER_CONTACT_CHANNELS

question: Compute the average active time span of contact channels.
query: SELECT AVG(EXTRACT(DAY FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) + EXTRACT(HOUR FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / 24 + EXTRACT(MINUTE FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / (24 * 60) + EXTRACT(SECOND FROM (ACTIVE_TO_DATE - ACTIVE_FROM_DATE)) / (24 * 60 * 60)) AS AVG_DAYS FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_ADDRESSES_CUSTOMER_CONTACT_CHANNELS

question: Show all train names and times in stations in London in descending order by train time.

question: Show the station name with greatest number of trains.

question: Show the station name with at least two trains.

question: What is the document status description of the document with id 1?
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_DOCUMENT_STATUS.DOCUMENT_STATUS_DESCRIPTION FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_DOCUMENT_STATUS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.DOCUMENT_STATUS_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_DOCUMENT_STATUS.DOCUMENT_STATUS_CODE WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.DOCUMENT_ID = 1

question: What is the name of the shipping agent of the document with id 2?
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.DOCUMENT_ID = 2

question: How many documents were shipped by USPS?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME = 'USPS'

question: Which shipping agent shipped the most documents? List the shipping agent name and the number of documents.
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME, COUNT(CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.DOCUMENT_ID) FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE GROUP BY CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME, CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE ORDER BY COUNT(CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.DOCUMENT_ID) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What address was the document with id 4 mailed to?
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_ADDRESSES.ADDRESS_DETAILS FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_ADDRESSES JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS_MAILED ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS_MAILED.MAILED_TO_ADDRESS_ID = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_ADDRESSES.ADDRESS_ID WHERE DOCUMENT_ID = 4

question: List the document ids of documents with the status done and type Paper, which not shipped by the shipping agent named USPS.
query: SELECT DOCUMENT_ID FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS WHERE DOCUMENT_STATUS_CODE = 'done' AND DOCUMENT_TYPE_CODE = 'Paper' MINUS SELECT DOCUMENT_ID FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME = 'USPS'

question: List document id of documents status is done and document type is Paper and the document is shipped by shipping agent named USPS.
query: SELECT DOCUMENT_ID FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS WHERE DOCUMENT_STATUS_CODE = 'done' AND DOCUMENT_TYPE_CODE = 'Paper' INTERSECT SELECT DOCUMENT_ID FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_DOCUMENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_CODE WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_REF_SHIPPING_AGENTS.SHIPPING_AGENT_NAME = 'USPS'

question: List all employees in the circulation history of the document with id 1. List the employee's name.
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_NAME FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.EMPLOYEE_ID = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_ID WHERE CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.DOCUMENT_ID = 1

question: List the employees who have not showed up in any circulation history of documents. List the employee's name.
query: SELECT EMPLOYEE_NAME FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES MINUS SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_NAME FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.EMPLOYEE_ID = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_ID

question: Which employee has showed up in most circulation history documents. List the employee's name and the number of drafts and copies.
query: SELECT CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_NAME, COUNT(*) FROM CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES JOIN CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY ON CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.EMPLOYEE_ID = CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_ID GROUP BY CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_EMPLOYEES.EMPLOYEE_NAME, CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.DOCUMENT_ID, CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.DRAFT_NUMBER, CRE_DOC_CONTROL_SYSTEMS_CIRCULATION_HISTORY.COPY_NUMBER ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Show the name of the customer who has the most orders.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Show the product type codes which have at least two products.

question: Show the names of customers who have both an order in completed status and an order in part status.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T2.ORDER_STATUS_CODE  =  'Completed' INTERSECT SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T2.ORDER_STATUS_CODE  =  'Part'

question: Show the minimum, maximum, average price for all products.

question: How many products have a price higher than the average?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_PRODUCTS WHERE PRODUCT_PRICE  >  (SELECT AVG(PRODUCT_PRICE) FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_PRODUCTS)

question: Show the names of customers who use Credit Card payment method and have more than 2 orders.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.PAYMENT_METHOD_CODE = 'Credit Card' GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_NAME, T1.CUSTOMER_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 2

question: What are the name and phone of the customer with the most ordered product quantity?
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME, T1.CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ORDERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_ORDER_ITEMS T3 ON T3.ORDER_ID = T2.ORDER_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_ID, T1.CUSTOMER_NAME, T1.CUSTOMER_PHONE ORDER BY SUM(CASE WHEN REGEXP_LIKE(T3.ORDER_QUANTITY, '^[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?$') THEN TO_NUMBER(T3.ORDER_QUANTITY) ELSE 0 END) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Show the product type and name for the products with price higher than 1000 or lower than 500.
query: SELECT PRODUCT_TYPE_CODE ,  PRODUCT_NAME FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_PRODUCTS WHERE PRODUCT_PRICE  >  1000 OR PRODUCT_PRICE  <  500

question: Show the product name and total order quantity for each product.
query: SELECT T1.PRODUCT_NAME, SUM(CASE WHEN REGEXP_LIKE(T2.ORDER_QUANTITY, '^[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?$') THEN TO_NUMBER(T2.ORDER_QUANTITY) ELSE 0 END) AS TOTAL_QUANTITY FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_PRODUCTS T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_ORDER_ITEMS T2 ON T1.PRODUCT_ID = T2.PRODUCT_ID GROUP BY T1.PRODUCT_NAME, T1.PRODUCT_ID

question: Show the customer name, customer address city, date from, and date to for each customer address history.
query: SELECT T2.CUSTOMER_NAME, T3.CITY, T1.DATE_FROM AS DATE_FROM, T1.DATE_TO AS DATE_TO FROM CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMER_ADDRESS_HISTORY T1 JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_CUSTOMERS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN CUSTOMERS_AND_PRODUCTS_CONTACTS_ADDRESSES T3 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID = T3.ADDRESS_ID

question: What are the ids and names of the architects who built at least 3 bridges ?
query: SELECT T1.ID, T1.NAME FROM ARCHITECTURE_ARCHITECT T1 JOIN ARCHITECTURE_BRIDGE T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ARCHITECT_ID GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.NAME HAVING COUNT(*) >= 3

question: What is the id, name and nationality of the architect who built most mills?
query: SELECT T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.NATIONALITY FROM (SELECT T1.ID AS ID, T1.NAME AS NAME, T1.NATIONALITY AS NATIONALITY, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM ARCHITECTURE_ARCHITECT T1 JOIN ARCHITECTURE_MILL T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ARCHITECT_ID GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.NATIONALITY ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) T1 WHERE ROWNUM = 1

question: What are the ids, names and genders of the architects who built two bridges or one mill?
query: SELECT T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.GENDER FROM ARCHITECTURE_ARCHITECT T1 JOIN ARCHITECTURE_BRIDGE T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ARCHITECT_ID GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.GENDER HAVING COUNT(*) = 2 UNION SELECT T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.GENDER FROM ARCHITECTURE_ARCHITECT T1 JOIN ARCHITECTURE_MILL T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ARCHITECT_ID GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.NAME, T1.GENDER HAVING COUNT(*) = 1

question: How many buildings are there?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING

question: Show the name, street address, and number of floors for all buildings ordered by the number of floors.
query: SELECT NAME ,  STREET_ADDRESS ,  FLOORS FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING ORDER BY FLOORS

question: What is the name of the tallest building?
query: SELECT NAME FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING ORDER BY HEIGHT_FEET DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are the average, maximum, and minimum number of floors for all buildings?
query: SELECT AVG(FLOORS) ,  MAX(FLOORS) ,  MIN(FLOORS) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING

question: Show the number of buildings with a height above the average or a number of floors above the average.
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING WHERE HEIGHT_FEET  >  (SELECT AVG(HEIGHT_FEET) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING) OR FLOORS  >  (SELECT AVG(FLOORS) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING)

question: List the names of buildings with at least 200 feet of height and with at least 20 floors.
query: SELECT NAME FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING WHERE HEIGHT_FEET  >=  200 AND FLOORS  >=  20

question: Show the names and locations of institutions that are founded after 1990 and have the type "Private".
query: SELECT INSTITUTION ,  LOCATION FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION WHERE FOUNDED  >  1990 AND TYPE  =  'Private'

question: Show institution types, along with the number of institutions and total enrollment for each type.
query: SELECT TYPE ,  COUNT(*) ,  SUM(ENROLLMENT) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION GROUP BY TYPE

question: Show the institution type with the largest number of institutions.
query: SELECT TYPE FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Show the institution type with an institution founded after 1990 and an institution with at least 1000 enrollment.
query: SELECT TYPE FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION WHERE FOUNDED  >  1990 AND ENROLLMENT  >=  1000

question: Show the name of buildings that do not have any institution.
query: SELECT NAME FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING WHERE BUILDING_ID NOT IN (SELECT BUILDING_ID FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION)

question: Show the names of buildings except for those having an institution founded in 2003.
query: SELECT NAME FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING MINUS SELECT T1.NAME FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T2 ON T1.BUILDING_ID  =  T2.BUILDING_ID WHERE T2.FOUNDED  =  2003

question: For each building, show the name of the building and the number of institutions in it.
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T2 ON T1.BUILDING_ID  =  T2.BUILDING_ID GROUP BY T1.NAME

question: Show the names and heights of buildings with at least two institutions founded after 1880.
query: SELECT T1.NAME, T1.HEIGHT_FEET FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T2 ON T1.BUILDING_ID = T2.BUILDING_ID WHERE T2.FOUNDED > 1880 GROUP BY T1.BUILDING_ID, T1.NAME, T1.HEIGHT_FEET HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2

question: Show all the distinct institution types.
query: SELECT DISTINCT TYPE FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION

question: Show institution names along with the number of proteins for each institution.
query: SELECT T1.INSTITUTION ,  COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_PROTEIN T2 ON T1.INSTITUTION_ID  =  T2.INSTITUTION_ID GROUP BY T1.INSTITUTION

question: How many proteins are associated with an institution founded after 1880 or an institution with type "Private"?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_PROTEIN T2 ON T1.INSTITUTION_ID  =  T2.INSTITUTION_ID WHERE T1.FOUNDED  >  1880 OR T1.TYPE  =  'Private'

question: Show the protein name and the institution name.
query: SELECT T2.PROTEIN_NAME ,  T1.INSTITUTION FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_PROTEIN T2 ON T1.INSTITUTION_ID  =  T2.INSTITUTION_ID

question: How many proteins are associated with an institution in a building with at least 20 floors?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION T1 JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_PROTEIN T2 ON T1.INSTITUTION_ID  =  T2.INSTITUTION_ID JOIN PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_BUILDING T3 ON T3.BUILDING_ID  =  T1.BUILDING_ID WHERE T3.FLOORS  >=  20

question: How many institutions do not have an associated protein in our record?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_INSTITUTION WHERE INSTITUTION_ID NOT IN (SELECT INSTITUTION_ID FROM PROTEIN_INSTITUTE_PROTEIN)

question: Which assets have 2 parts and have less than 2 fault logs? List the asset id and detail.
query: SELECT T1.ASSET_ID, T1.ASSET_DETAILS FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSET_PARTS T2 ON T1.ASSET_ID = T2.ASSET_ID GROUP BY T1.ASSET_ID, T1.ASSET_DETAILS HAVING COUNT(*) = 2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.ASSET_ID, T1.ASSET_DETAILS FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG T2 ON T1.ASSET_ID = T2.ASSET_ID GROUP BY T1.ASSET_ID, T1.ASSET_DETAILS HAVING COUNT(*) < 2

question: How many assets does each maintenance contract contain? List the number and the contract id.
query: SELECT COUNT(*) ,  T1.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_CONTRACTS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS T2 ON T1.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_ID  =  T2.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_ID GROUP BY T1.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_ID

question: How many assets does each third party company supply? List the count and the company id.
query: SELECT COUNT(*) ,  T1.COMPANY_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_THIRD_PARTY_COMPANIES T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS T2 ON T1.COMPANY_ID  =  T2.SUPPLIER_COMPANY_ID GROUP BY T1.COMPANY_ID

question: Which third party companies have at least 2 maintenance engineers or have at least 2 maintenance contracts? List the company id and name.
query: SELECT T1.COMPANY_ID, T1.COMPANY_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_THIRD_PARTY_COMPANIES T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS T2 ON T1.COMPANY_ID = T2.COMPANY_ID GROUP BY T1.COMPANY_ID, T1.COMPANY_NAME HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2 UNION SELECT T3.COMPANY_ID, T3.COMPANY_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_THIRD_PARTY_COMPANIES T3 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_CONTRACTS T4 ON T3.COMPANY_ID = T4.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_COMPANY_ID GROUP BY T3.COMPANY_ID, T3.COMPANY_NAME HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2

question: What is the name and id of the staff who recorded the fault log but has not contacted any visiting engineers?
query: SELECT T1.STAFF_NAME ,  T1.STAFF_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_STAFF T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG T2 ON T1.STAFF_ID  =  T2.RECORDED_BY_STAFF_ID MINUS SELECT T3.STAFF_NAME ,  T3.STAFF_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_STAFF T3 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T4 ON T3.STAFF_ID  =  T4.CONTACT_STAFF_ID

question: Which parts have more than 2 faults? Show the part name and id.
query: SELECT T1.PART_NAME ,  T1.PART_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PARTS  T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PART_FAULTS  T2 ON T1.PART_ID  =  T2.PART_ID GROUP BY T1.PART_ID, T1.PART_NAME HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

question: List all every engineer's first name, last name, details and coresponding skill description.
query: SELECT T1.FIRST_NAME ,  T1.LAST_NAME ,  T1.OTHER_DETAILS ,  T3.SKILL_DESCRIPTION FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_SKILLS T2 ON T1.ENGINEER_ID  =  T2.ENGINEER_ID JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS T3 ON T2.SKILL_ID  =  T3.SKILL_ID

question: For all the faults of different parts, what are all the decriptions of the skills required to fix them? List the name of the faults and the skill description.
query: SELECT T1.FAULT_SHORT_NAME ,  T3.SKILL_DESCRIPTION FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PART_FAULTS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS_REQUIRED_TO_FIX T2 ON T1.PART_FAULT_ID  =  T2.PART_FAULT_ID JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS T3 ON T2.SKILL_ID  =  T3.SKILL_ID

question: How many assets can each parts be used in? List the part name and the number.
query: SELECT T1.PART_NAME ,  COUNT(*) FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PARTS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSET_PARTS T2 ON T1.PART_ID  =  T2.PART_ID GROUP BY T1.PART_NAME

question: What are all the fault descriptions and the fault status of all the faults recoreded in the logs?
query: SELECT T1.FAULT_DESCRIPTION ,  T2.FAULT_STATUS FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG_PARTS T2 ON T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID  =  T2.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID

question: How many engineer visits are required at most for a single fault log? List the number and the log entry id.
query: SELECT COUNT(*) ,  T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T2 ON T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID  =  T2.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID GROUP BY T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are all the distinct last names of all the engineers?
query: SELECT DISTINCT LAST_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS

question: How many fault status codes are recorded in the fault log parts table?
query: SELECT DISTINCT FAULT_STATUS FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG_PARTS

question: Which engineers have never visited to maintain the assets? List the engineer first name and last name.
query: SELECT FIRST_NAME ,  LAST_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS WHERE ENGINEER_ID NOT IN (SELECT ENGINEER_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS)

question: List the asset id, details, make and model for every asset.
query: SELECT ASSET_ID ,  ASSET_DETAILS ,  ASSET_MAKE ,  ASSET_MODEL FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS

question: When was the first asset acquired?
query: SELECT ASSET_ACQUIRED_DATE FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS ORDER BY ASSET_ACQUIRED_DATE ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Which part fault requires the most number of skills to fix? List part id and name.
query: SELECT T1.PART_ID, T1.PART_NAME FROM (SELECT T1.PART_ID, T1.PART_NAME, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PARTS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PART_FAULTS T2 ON T1.PART_ID = T2.PART_ID JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS_REQUIRED_TO_FIX T3 ON T2.PART_FAULT_ID = T3.PART_FAULT_ID GROUP BY T1.PART_ID, T1.PART_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) T1 WHERE ROWNUM = 1

question: Which kind of part has the least number of faults? List the part name.
query: SELECT T1.PART_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PARTS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PART_FAULTS T2 ON T1.PART_ID  =  T2.PART_ID GROUP BY T1.PART_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Among those engineers who have visited, which engineer makes the least number of visits? List the engineer id, first name and last name.
query: SELECT T1.ENGINEER_ID, T1.FIRST_NAME, T1.LAST_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T2 ON T1.ENGINEER_ID = T2.ENGINEER_ID GROUP BY T1.ENGINEER_ID, T1.FIRST_NAME, T1.LAST_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Which staff have contacted which engineers? List the staff name and the engineer first name and last name.
query: SELECT T1.STAFF_NAME ,  T3.FIRST_NAME ,  T3.LAST_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_STAFF T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T2 ON T1.STAFF_ID  =  T2.CONTACT_STAFF_ID JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS T3 ON T2.ENGINEER_ID  =  T3.ENGINEER_ID

question: Which skill is used in fixing the most number of faults? List the skill id and description.
query: SELECT T1.SKILL_ID, T1.SKILL_DESCRIPTION FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_SKILLS_REQUIRED_TO_FIX T2 ON T1.SKILL_ID = T2.SKILL_ID GROUP BY T1.SKILL_ID, T1.SKILL_DESCRIPTION ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are all the distinct asset models?
query: SELECT DISTINCT ASSET_MODEL FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS

question: List the all the assets make, model, details by the disposed date ascendingly.
query: SELECT ASSET_MAKE ,  ASSET_MODEL ,  ASSET_DETAILS FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS ORDER BY ASSET_DISPOSED_DATE ASC

question: Which part has the least chargeable amount? List the part id and amount.
query: SELECT PART_ID ,  CHARGEABLE_AMOUNT FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_PARTS ORDER BY CHARGEABLE_AMOUNT ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Which company started the earliest the maintenance contract? Show the company name.
query: SELECT T1.COMPANY_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_THIRD_PARTY_COMPANIES T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_CONTRACTS T2 ON T1.COMPANY_ID  =  T2.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_COMPANY_ID ORDER BY T2.CONTRACT_START_DATE ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Which gender makes up the majority of the staff?
query: SELECT GENDER FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_STAFF GROUP BY GENDER ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: How many engineers did each staff contact? List both the contact staff name and number of engineers contacted.
query: SELECT T1.STAFF_NAME ,  COUNT(*) FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_STAFF T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T2 ON T1.STAFF_ID  =  T2.CONTACT_STAFF_ID GROUP BY T1.STAFF_NAME

question: Which assets did not incur any fault log? List the asset model.
query: SELECT ASSET_MODEL FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ASSETS WHERE ASSET_ID NOT IN (SELECT ASSET_ID FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG)

question: Which engineer has visited the most times? Show the engineer id, first name and last name.
query: SELECT T2.ENGINEER_ID, T1.FIRST_NAME, T1.LAST_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEERS T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_ENGINEER_VISITS T2 ON T1.ENGINEER_ID = T2.ENGINEER_ID GROUP BY T2.ENGINEER_ID, T1.FIRST_NAME, T1.LAST_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY

question: Which fault log included the most number of faulty parts? List the fault log id, description and record time.
query: SELECT T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID, T1.FAULT_DESCRIPTION, T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_DATETIME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_FAULT_LOG_PARTS T2 ON T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID = T2.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID GROUP BY T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_ID, T1.FAULT_DESCRIPTION, T1.FAULT_LOG_ENTRY_DATETIME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What is the description of the type of the company who concluded its contracts most recently?
query: SELECT T1.COMPANY_NAME FROM ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_THIRD_PARTY_COMPANIES T1 JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_MAINTENANCE_CONTRACTS T2 ON T1.COMPANY_ID = T2.MAINTENANCE_CONTRACT_COMPANY_ID JOIN ASSETS_MAINTENANCE_REF_COMPANY_TYPES T3 ON T1.COMPANY_TYPE = T3.COMPANY_TYPE_CODE ORDER BY T2.CONTRACT_END_DATE DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: How many residents does each property have? List property id and resident count.
query: SELECT T1.PROPERTY_ID ,  COUNT(*) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_PROPERTIES T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS T2 ON T1.PROPERTY_ID  =  T2.PROPERTY_ID GROUP BY T1.PROPERTY_ID

question: What is the distinct service types that are provided by the organization which has detail 'Denesik and Sons Party'?
query: SELECT DISTINCT T1.SERVICE_TYPE_CODE FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_SERVICES T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_ORGANIZATIONS T2 ON T1.ORGANIZATION_ID  =  T2.ORGANIZATION_ID WHERE T2.ORGANIZATION_DETAILS  =  'Denesik and Sons Party'

question: How many services has each resident requested? List the resident id, details, and the count in descending order of the count.
query: SELECT T1.RESIDENT_ID ,  T1.OTHER_DETAILS ,  COUNT(*) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS_SERVICES T2 ON T1.RESIDENT_ID  =  T2.RESIDENT_ID GROUP BY T1.RESIDENT_ID, T1.OTHER_DETAILS

question: What is the maximum number that a certain service is provided? List the service id, details and number.
query: SELECT T1.SERVICE_ID, T1.SERVICE_DETAILS, COUNT(*) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_SERVICES T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS_SERVICES T2 ON T1.SERVICE_ID = T2.SERVICE_ID GROUP BY T1.SERVICE_ID, T1.SERVICE_DETAILS ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: List the id and type of each thing, and the details of the organization that owns it.
query: SELECT T1.THING_ID ,  T1.TYPE_OF_THING_CODE ,  T2.ORGANIZATION_DETAILS FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_THINGS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_ORGANIZATIONS T2 ON T1.ORGANIZATION_ID  =  T2.ORGANIZATION_ID

question: What are the id and details of the customers who have at least 3 events?
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_ID, T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENTS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_ID, T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS HAVING COUNT(*) >= 3

question: Which events have the number of notes between one and three? List the event id and the property id.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_EVENT_ID  ,  T1.PROPERTY_ID FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENTS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENT_NOTES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_EVENT_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_EVENT_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_EVENT_ID, T1.PROPERTY_ID

question: How many distinct locations have the things with service detail 'Unsatisfied' been located in?
query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.LOCATION_CODE) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_THINGS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_TIMED_LOCATIONS_OF_THINGS T2 ON T1.THING_ID  =  T2.THING_ID WHERE T1.SERVICE_DETAILS  =  'Unsatisfied'

question: How many different status codes of things are there?
query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT STATUS_OF_THING_CODE) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_TIMED_STATUS_OF_THINGS

question: Which organizations are not a parent organization of others? List the organization id.
query: SELECT ORGANIZATION_ID FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_ORGANIZATIONS MINUS SELECT PARENT_ORGANIZATION_ID FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_ORGANIZATIONS

question: What are the resident details containing the substring 'Miss'?
query: SELECT OTHER_DETAILS FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS WHERE UPPER(OTHER_DETAILS) LIKE UPPER('%Miss%')

question: List the customer event id and the corresponding move in date and property id.
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_EVENT_ID ,  DATE_MOVED_IN ,  PROPERTY_ID FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENTS

question: How many customers did not have any event?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMERS WHERE CUSTOMER_ID NOT IN ( SELECT CUSTOMER_ID FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENTS )

question: What are the distinct move in dates of the residents?
query: SELECT DISTINCT DATE_MOVED_IN FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS

question: What is each customer's move in date, and the corresponding customer id and details?
query: SELECT T2.DATE_MOVED_IN, T1.CUSTOMER_ID, T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_CUSTOMER_EVENTS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID = T2.CUSTOMER_ID

question: What are the distinct id and type of the thing that has the status 'Close' or has a status record before the date '2017-06-19 02:59:21'
query: SELECT DISTINCT T2.THING_ID, T2.TYPE_OF_THING_CODE FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_TIMED_STATUS_OF_THINGS T1 JOIN LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_THINGS T2 ON T1.THING_ID = T2.THING_ID WHERE T1.STATUS_OF_THING_CODE = 'Close' OR T1.DATE_AND_DATE < TIMESTAMP '2017-06-19 02:59:21'

question: When is the last day any resident moved in?
query: SELECT MAX(DATE_MOVED_IN) FROM LOCAL_GOVT_AND_LOT_RESIDENTS

question: Find all the phone numbers.
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES

question: What are all the phone numbers?
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES

question: What are the customer phone numbers under the policy "Life Insurance"?
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES WHERE POLICY_TYPE_CODE  =  'Life Insurance'

question: What are the phone numbers of customers using the policy with the code "Life Insurance"?
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES WHERE POLICY_TYPE_CODE  =  'Life Insurance'

question: Which policy type has the most records in the database?
query: SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Which policy type appears most frequently in the available policies?
query: SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are all the customer phone numbers under the most popular policy type?
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES WHERE POLICY_TYPE_CODE  =  (SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY)

question: Find the phone numbers of customers using the most common policy type among the available policies.
query: SELECT CUSTOMER_PHONE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES WHERE POLICY_TYPE_CODE  =  (SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY)

question: Find the policy type used by more than 4 customers.
query: SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE HAVING COUNT(*)  >  4

question: Find the policy types more than 4 customers use. Show their type code.
query: SELECT POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES GROUP BY POLICY_TYPE_CODE HAVING COUNT(*)  >  4

question: Find the total and average amount of settlements.
query: SELECT SUM(SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) ,  AVG(SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_SETTLEMENTS

question: Return the sum and average of all settlement amounts.
query: SELECT SUM(SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) ,  AVG(SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_SETTLEMENTS

question: Find the name of services that have been used for more than 2 times in first notification of loss.
query: SELECT T2.SERVICE_NAME FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_FIRST_NOTIFICATION_OF_LOSS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SERVICES T2 ON T1.SERVICE_ID = T2.SERVICE_ID GROUP BY T2.SERVICE_NAME, T1.SERVICE_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 2

question: Which services have been used more than twice in first notification of loss? Return the service name.
query: SELECT T2.SERVICE_NAME FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_FIRST_NOTIFICATION_OF_LOSS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SERVICES T2 ON T1.SERVICE_ID = T2.SERVICE_ID GROUP BY T2.SERVICE_NAME, T1.SERVICE_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 2

question: What is the effective date of the claim that has the largest amount of total settlement?
query: SELECT T1.EFFECTIVE_DATE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CLAIMS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SETTLEMENTS T2 ON T1.CLAIM_ID = T2.CLAIM_ID GROUP BY T1.CLAIM_ID, T1.EFFECTIVE_DATE ORDER BY SUM(T2.SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Find the claim that has the largest total settlement amount. Return the effective date of the claim.
query: SELECT T1.EFFECTIVE_DATE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CLAIMS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SETTLEMENTS T2 ON T1.CLAIM_ID = T2.CLAIM_ID GROUP BY T1.CLAIM_ID, T1.EFFECTIVE_DATE ORDER BY SUM(T2.SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: How many policies are listed for the customer named "Dayana Robel"?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS_POLICIES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.CUSTOMER_NAME  =  'Dayana Robel'

question: Count the total number of policies used by the customer named "Dayana Robel".
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS_POLICIES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID WHERE T1.CUSTOMER_NAME  =  'Dayana Robel'

question: What is the name of the customer who has the most policies listed?

question: What are all the policy types of the customer named "Dayana Robel"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT T3.POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS_POLICIES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES T3 ON T2.POLICY_ID  =  T3.POLICY_ID WHERE T1.CUSTOMER_NAME  =  'Dayana Robel'

question: Tell me the types of the policy used by the customer named "Dayana Robel".

question: What are all the policy types of the customer that has the most policies listed?
query: SELECT DISTINCT T3.POLICY_TYPE_CODE FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS_POLICIES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_AVAILABLE_POLICIES T3 ON T2.POLICY_ID  =  T3.POLICY_ID WHERE T1.CUSTOMER_NAME  =  (SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS_POLICIES T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_NAME ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY)

question: List all the policy types used by the customer enrolled in the most policies.

question: Find the names of customers who have used either the service "Close a policy" or the service "Upgrade a policy".

question: Find the names of customers who have used both the service "Close a policy" and the service "New policy application".
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_FIRST_NOTIFICATION_OF_LOSS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SERVICES T3 ON T2.SERVICE_ID  =  T3.SERVICE_ID WHERE T3.SERVICE_NAME  =  'Close a policy' INTERSECT SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_NAME FROM INSURANCE_FNOL_CUSTOMERS T1 JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_FIRST_NOTIFICATION_OF_LOSS T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN INSURANCE_FNOL_SERVICES T3 ON T2.SERVICE_ID  =  T3.SERVICE_ID WHERE T3.SERVICE_NAME  =  'New policy application'

question: Which customers have used both the service named "Close a policy" and the service named "Upgrade a policy"? Give me the customer names.

question: Find the personal name, family name, and author ID of the course author that teaches the most courses.

question: What are the student IDs and middle names of the students enrolled in at most two courses?
query: SELECT T1.STUDENT_ID, T2.MIDDLE_NAME FROM E_LEARNING_STUDENT_COURSE_ENROLMENT T1 JOIN E_LEARNING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID GROUP BY T1.STUDENT_ID, T2.MIDDLE_NAME HAVING COUNT(*) <= 2

question: Find the personal names of students not enrolled in any course.
query: SELECT PERSONAL_NAME FROM E_LEARNING_STUDENTS MINUS SELECT T1.PERSONAL_NAME FROM E_LEARNING_STUDENTS T1 JOIN E_LEARNING_STUDENT_COURSE_ENROLMENT T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID  =  T2.STUDENT_ID

question: Which students not enrolled in any course? Find their personal names.

question: How many students did not have any course enrollment?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM E_LEARNING_STUDENTS WHERE STUDENT_ID NOT IN (SELECT STUDENT_ID FROM E_LEARNING_STUDENT_COURSE_ENROLMENT)

question: Find the id and first name of the student that has the most number of assessment notes?
query: SELECT T1.STUDENT_ID, T2.FIRST_NAME FROM (SELECT STUDENT_ID, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ASSESSMENT_NOTES GROUP BY STUDENT_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY) T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID

question: Find the ids and first names of the 3 teachers that have the most number of assessment notes?
query: SELECT T1.TEACHER_ID, T2.FIRST_NAME FROM (SELECT TEACHER_ID, COUNT(*) AS CNT FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ASSESSMENT_NOTES GROUP BY TEACHER_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 3 ROWS ONLY) T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.TEACHER_ID = T2.TEACHER_ID ORDER BY T1.CNT DESC

question: Find the id and last name of the student that has the most behavior incidents?
query: SELECT T1.STUDENT_ID, T2.LAST_NAME FROM (SELECT STUDENT_ID, COUNT(*) AS INCIDENT_COUNT FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_BEHAVIOR_INCIDENT GROUP BY STUDENT_ID ORDER BY INCIDENT_COUNT DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY) T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID

question: Find the id and last name of the teacher that has the most detentions with detention type code "AFTER"?
query: SELECT TEACHER_ID, LAST_NAME FROM (    SELECT T1.TEACHER_ID, T2.LAST_NAME, COUNT(*) AS CNT     FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_DETENTION T1     JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.TEACHER_ID = T2.TEACHER_ID     WHERE T1.DETENTION_TYPE_CODE = 'AFTER'     GROUP BY T1.TEACHER_ID, T2.LAST_NAME     ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC ) WHERE ROWNUM = 1

question: What are the id and first name of the student whose addresses have the highest average monthly rental?
query: SELECT T1.STUDENT_ID, T2.FIRST_NAME FROM (SELECT STUDENT_ID, AVG(MONTHLY_RENTAL) AS AVG_RENTAL FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES GROUP BY STUDENT_ID ORDER BY AVG(MONTHLY_RENTAL) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY) T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID

question: Find the id and city of the student address with the highest average monthly rental.
query: SELECT T2.ADDRESS_ID, T1.CITY FROM (SELECT ADDRESS_ID, CITY FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES) T1 JOIN (SELECT ADDRESS_ID, AVG(MONTHLY_RENTAL) AS AVG_RENTAL FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES GROUP BY ADDRESS_ID) T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID = T2.ADDRESS_ID ORDER BY T2.AVG_RENTAL DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Find the texts of assessment notes for teachers with last name "Schuster".
query: SELECT T1.TEXT_OF_NOTES FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ASSESSMENT_NOTES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.TEACHER_ID  =  T2.TEACHER_ID WHERE T2.LAST_NAME  =  'Schuster'

question: What are the id and zip code of the address with the highest monthly rental?
query: SELECT T2.ADDRESS_ID ,  T1.ZIP_POSTCODE FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID ORDER BY MONTHLY_RENTAL DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What is the cell phone number of the student whose address has the lowest monthly rental?
query: SELECT T2.CELL_MOBILE_NUMBER FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID  =  T2.STUDENT_ID ORDER BY T1.MONTHLY_RENTAL ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are the monthly rentals of student addresses in Texas state?
query: SELECT T2.MONTHLY_RENTAL FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID WHERE T1.STATE_PROVINCE_COUNTY  =  'Texas'

question: What are the first names and last names of students with address in Wisconsin state?
query: SELECT T2.FIRST_NAME ,  T2.LAST_NAME FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID WHERE T1.STATE_PROVINCE_COUNTY  =  'Wisconsin'

question: What are the line 1 and average monthly rentals of all student addresses?
query: SELECT T1.LINE_1 ,  AVG(T2.MONTHLY_RENTAL) FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENT_ADDRESSES T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID GROUP BY T1.LINE_1

question: What is the zip code of the address where the teacher with first name "Lyla" lives?
query: SELECT T1.ZIP_POSTCODE FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID WHERE T2.FIRST_NAME  =  'Lyla'

question: What are the email addresses of teachers whose address has zip code "918"?
query: SELECT T2.EMAIL_ADDRESS FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID WHERE T1.ZIP_POSTCODE  =  '918'

question: Find the last names of teachers who are not involved in any detention.
query: SELECT LAST_NAME FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS MINUS SELECT T1.LAST_NAME FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_DETENTION T2 ON T1.TEACHER_ID  =  T2.TEACHER_ID

question: What are the line 1 of addresses shared by some students and some teachers?
query: SELECT T1.LINE_1 FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID INTERSECT SELECT T1.LINE_1 FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ADDRESSES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.ADDRESS_ID  =  T2.ADDRESS_ID

question: What is the incident type description for the incident type with code "VIOLENCE"?
query: SELECT INCIDENT_TYPE_DESCRIPTION FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_REF_INCIDENT_TYPE WHERE INCIDENT_TYPE_CODE = 'VIOLENCE'

question: What are the code and description of the most frequent behavior incident type?
query: SELECT T1.INCIDENT_TYPE_CODE, T2.INCIDENT_TYPE_DESCRIPTION FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_BEHAVIOR_INCIDENT T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_REF_INCIDENT_TYPE T2 ON T1.INCIDENT_TYPE_CODE = T2.INCIDENT_TYPE_CODE GROUP BY T1.INCIDENT_TYPE_CODE, T2.INCIDENT_TYPE_DESCRIPTION ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What are the code and description of the least frequent detention type ?
query: SELECT T1.DETENTION_TYPE_CODE, T2.DETENTION_TYPE_DESCRIPTION FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_DETENTION T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_REF_DETENTION_TYPE T2 ON T1.DETENTION_TYPE_CODE = T2.DETENTION_TYPE_CODE GROUP BY T1.DETENTION_TYPE_CODE, T2.DETENTION_TYPE_DESCRIPTION ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Find the dates of assessment notes for students with first name "Fanny".
query: SELECT T1.DATE_OF_NOTES FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_ASSESSMENT_NOTES T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID WHERE T2.FIRST_NAME = 'Fanny'

question: Find the start and end dates of behavior incidents of students with last name "Fahey".
query: SELECT T1.DATE_INCIDENT_START, T1.DATE_INCIDENT_END FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_BEHAVIOR_INCIDENT T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_STUDENTS T2 ON T1.STUDENT_ID = T2.STUDENT_ID WHERE T2.LAST_NAME = 'Fahey'

question: Find the start and end dates of detentions of teachers with last name "Schultz".
query: SELECT T1.DATETIME_DETENTION_START, T1.DATETIME_DETENTION_END FROM BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_DETENTION T1 JOIN BEHAVIOR_MONITORING_TEACHERS T2 ON T1.TEACHER_ID = T2.TEACHER_ID WHERE T2.LAST_NAME = 'Schultz'

question: Show the names of countries and the average speed of roller coasters from each country.
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  AVG(T2.SPEED) FROM ROLLER_COASTER_COUNTRY T1 JOIN ROLLER_COASTER_ROLLER_COASTER T2 ON T1.COUNTRY_ID  =  T2.COUNTRY_ID GROUP BY T1.NAME

question: How many countries do not have an roller coaster longer than 3000?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ROLLER_COASTER_COUNTRY WHERE COUNTRY_ID NOT IN ( SELECT COUNTRY_ID FROM ROLLER_COASTER_ROLLER_COASTER WHERE LENGTH  >  3000 )

question: What are the country names, area and population which has both roller coasters with speed higher
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  T1.AREA ,  T1.POPULATION FROM ROLLER_COASTER_COUNTRY T1 JOIN ROLLER_COASTER_ROLLER_COASTER T2 ON T1.COUNTRY_ID  =  T2.COUNTRY_ID WHERE T2.SPEED  >  60 INTERSECT SELECT T1.NAME ,  T1.AREA ,  T1.POPULATION FROM ROLLER_COASTER_COUNTRY T1 JOIN ROLLER_COASTER_ROLLER_COASTER T2 ON T1.COUNTRY_ID  =  T2.COUNTRY_ID WHERE T2.SPEED  <  55

question: Find the total savings balance of all accounts except the account with name ‘Brown’.
query: SELECT SUM(T2.BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T1.NAME != 'Brown'

question: What is the total balance of savings accounts not belonging to someone with the name Brown?

question: How many accounts are there in total?
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS

question: Count the number of accounts.
query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS

question: What is the total checking balance in all accounts?
query: SELECT SUM(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING

question: Find the total balance across checking accounts.
query: SELECT SUM(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING

question: Find the average checking balance.
query: SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING

question: What is the average balance in checking accounts?
query: SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING

question: How many accounts have a savings balance above the average savings balance?

question: Find the number of accounts with a savings balance that is higher than the average savings balance.

question: Find the name and id of accounts whose checking balance is below the maximum checking balance.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTID ,  T1.NAME FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T2.BALANCE  <  (SELECT MAX(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING)

question: What are the customer id and name corresponding to accounts with a checking balance less than the largest checking balance?

question: What is the checking balance of the account whose owner’s name contains the substring ‘ee’?

question: Find the balance of the checking account belonging to an owner whose name contains 'ee'.

question: Find the checking balance and saving balance in the Brown’s account.

question: What are the checking and savings balances in accounts belonging to Brown?
query: SELECT T2.BALANCE AS CHECKING_BALANCE,  T3.BALANCE AS SAVINGS_BALANCE FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T3 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T3.CUSTID WHERE T1.NAME  =  'Brown'

question: Find the names of accounts whose checking balance is above the average checking balance, but savings balance is below the average savings balance.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T2.BALANCE  >  (SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING) INTERSECT SELECT T1.NAME FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T2.BALANCE  <  (SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS)

question: What are the names of accounts with checking balances greater than the average checking balance and savings balances below the average savings balance?

question: Find the checking balance of the accounts whose savings balance is higher than the average savings balance.
query: SELECT T2.BALANCE FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T1.NAME IN (SELECT T1.NAME FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T2.BALANCE  >  (SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS))

question: What are the balances of checking accounts belonging to people with savings balances greater than the average savings balance?
query: SELECT T2.BALANCE FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T1.NAME IN (SELECT T1.NAME FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID WHERE T2.BALANCE  >  (SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS))

question: What are the names and sum of checking and savings balances for accounts with savings balances higher than the average savings balance?
query: SELECT T1.NAME ,  T2.BALANCE + T3.BALANCE FROM SMALL_BANK_1_ACCOUNTS T1 JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_CHECKING T2 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T2.CUSTID JOIN SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS T3 ON T1.CUSTID  =  T3.CUSTID WHERE T3.BALANCE  >  (SELECT AVG(BALANCE) FROM SMALL_BANK_1_SAVINGS)

question: Find the name and checking balance of the account with the lowest savings balance.

question: Find the name of accounts whose checking balance is below the average checking balance.

question: Find the saving balance of the account with the highest checking balance.

question: Show the ids for all the faculty members who have at least 2 students.

question: Find the first names of the faculty members who are playing Canoeing or Kayaking.
query: SELECT DISTINCT T1.LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY T1 JOIN ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY_PARTICIPATES_IN T2 ON T1.FACID  =  T2.FACID JOIN ACTIVITY_1_ACTIVITY T3 ON T2.ACTID  =  T2.ACTID WHERE T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Canoeing' OR T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Kayaking'

question: Which faculty members are playing either Canoeing or Kayaking? Tell me their first names.
query: SELECT DISTINCT T1.LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY T1 JOIN ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY_PARTICIPATES_IN T2 ON T1.FACID  =  T2.FACID JOIN ACTIVITY_1_ACTIVITY T3 ON T2.ACTID  =  T2.ACTID WHERE T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Canoeing' OR T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Kayaking'

question: Find the first names of professors who are not playing Canoeing or Kayaking.
query: SELECT LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY WHERE RANK  =  'Professor' MINUS SELECT DISTINCT T1.LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY T1 JOIN ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY_PARTICIPATES_IN T2 ON T1.FACID  =  T2.FACID JOIN ACTIVITY_1_ACTIVITY T3 ON T2.ACTID  =  T2.ACTID WHERE T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Canoeing' OR T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Kayaking'

query: SELECT LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY WHERE RANK  =  'Professor' MINUS SELECT DISTINCT T1.LNAME FROM ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY T1 JOIN ACTIVITY_1_FACULTY_PARTICIPATES_IN T2 ON T1.FACID  =  T2.FACID JOIN ACTIVITY_1_ACTIVITY T3 ON T2.ACTID  =  T2.ACTID WHERE T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Canoeing' OR T3.ACTIVITY_NAME  =  'Kayaking'

question: Find the first names of the faculty members who participate in Canoeing and Kayaking.

question: Find the ids of the students who participate in Canoeing and Kayaking.

question: Find the name of the project for which a scientist whose name contains ‘Smith’ is assigned to.

question: Who has friends that are younger than the average age?
query: SELECT DISTINCT T2.NAME FROM NETWORK_2_PERSON T1 JOIN NETWORK_2_PERSONFRIEND T2 ON T1.NAME  =  T2.FRIEND WHERE T1.AGE  <  (SELECT AVG(AGE) FROM NETWORK_2_PERSON)

question: What are the different names of friends who are younger than the average age for a friend?

question: Who has friends that are older than the average age? Print their friends and their ages as well

question: Whare the names, friends, and ages of all people who are older than the average age of a person?

question: List the project details of the project both producing patent and paper as outcomes.
query: SELECT T1.PROJECT_DETAILS FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_PROJECTS T1 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_PROJECT_OUTCOMES T2 ON T1.PROJECT_ID  =  T2.PROJECT_ID WHERE T2.OUTCOME_CODE  =  'Paper' INTERSECT SELECT T1.PROJECT_DETAILS FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_PROJECTS T1 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_PROJECT_OUTCOMES T2 ON T1.PROJECT_ID  =  T2.PROJECT_ID WHERE T2.OUTCOME_CODE  =  'Patent'

question: What are the details of the project that is producing both patents and papers as outcomes?

question: Find the organisation ids and details of the organisations which are involved in
query: SELECT T2.ORGANISATION_ID ,  T2.ORGANISATION_DETAILS FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_GRANTS  T1 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_ORGANISATIONS  T2 ON T1.ORGANISATION_ID  =  T2.ORGANISATION_ID GROUP BY T2.ORGANISATION_DETAILS, T2.ORGANISATION_ID HAVING SUM(T1.GRANT_AMOUNT)  >  6000

question: What are the ids and details for all organizations that have grants of more than 6000 dollars?
query: SELECT T2.ORGANISATION_ID ,  T2.ORGANISATION_DETAILS FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_GRANTS  T1 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_ORGANISATIONS  T2 ON T1.ORGANISATION_ID  =  T2.ORGANISATION_ID GROUP BY T2.ORGANISATION_DETAILS, T2.ORGANISATION_ID HAVING SUM(T1.GRANT_AMOUNT)  >  6000

question: What is the organisation type and id of the organisation which has the most number of research staff?
query: SELECT T1.ORGANISATION_TYPE, T1.ORGANISATION_ID FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_ORGANISATIONS T1 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_RESEARCH_STAFF T2 ON T1.ORGANISATION_ID = T2.EMPLOYER_ORGANISATION_ID GROUP BY T1.ORGANISATION_TYPE, T1.ORGANISATION_ID HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(*)) FROM TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_ORGANISATIONS T3 JOIN TRACKING_GRANTS_FOR_RESEARCH_RESEARCH_STAFF T4 ON T3.ORGANISATION_ID = T4.EMPLOYER_ORGANISATION_ID GROUP BY T3.ORGANISATION_ID) FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY

question: What is the type and id of the organization that has the most research staff?

question: What are the task details, task id and project id for the projects which are detailed as 'omnis' or  have more than 2 outcomes?

question: What are the task details, task ids, and project ids for the progrects that are detailed as 'omnis' or have at least 3 outcomes?

question: Which customer had at least 2 policies but did not file any claims? List the customer details and id.
query: SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS ,  T1.CUSTOMER_ID FROM INSURANCE_POLICIES_CUSTOMERS  T1 JOIN INSURANCE_POLICIES_CUSTOMER_POLICIES  T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID GROUP BY T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS, T1.CUSTOMER_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2 MINUS  SELECT T1.CUSTOMER_DETAILS ,  T1.CUSTOMER_ID FROM INSURANCE_POLICIES_CUSTOMERS  T1 JOIN INSURANCE_POLICIES_CUSTOMER_POLICIES  T2 ON T1.CUSTOMER_ID  =  T2.CUSTOMER_ID JOIN INSURANCE_POLICIES_CLAIMS  T3 ON T2.POLICY_ID  =  T3.POLICY_ID

query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID = T2.SHIP_ID GROUP BY T1.NAME, T2.SHIP_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 1

question: what are the names and classes of the ships that do not have any captain yet?
query: SELECT NAME ,  CLASS FROM SHIP_1_SHIP WHERE SHIP_ID NOT IN (SELECT SHIP_ID FROM SHIP_1_CAPTAIN)

question: Return the names and classes of ships that do not have a captain?
query: SELECT NAME ,  CLASS FROM SHIP_1_SHIP WHERE SHIP_ID NOT IN (SELECT SHIP_ID FROM SHIP_1_CAPTAIN)

question: Find the name of the ship that is steered by the youngest captain.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID ORDER BY T2.AGE FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: What is the name of the ship that is commanded by the youngest captain?
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID ORDER BY T2.AGE FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Find the name and flag of ships that are not steered by any captain with Midshipman rank.
query: SELECT NAME ,  FLAG FROM SHIP_1_SHIP WHERE SHIP_ID NOT IN (SELECT SHIP_ID FROM SHIP_1_CAPTAIN WHERE RANK  =  'Midshipman')

question: What are the names and flags of ships that do not have a captain with the rank of Midshipman?
query: SELECT NAME ,  FLAG FROM SHIP_1_SHIP WHERE SHIP_ID NOT IN (SELECT SHIP_ID FROM SHIP_1_CAPTAIN WHERE RANK  =  'Midshipman')

question: Find the name of the ships that are steered by both a captain with Midshipman rank and a captain with Lieutenant rank.
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID WHERE T2.RANK  =  'Midshipman' INTERSECT SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID WHERE T2.RANK  =  'Lieutenant'

question: What are the names of ships that are commanded by both captains with the rank of Midshipman and captains with the rank of Lieutenant?
query: SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID WHERE T2.RANK  =  'Midshipman' INTERSECT SELECT T1.NAME FROM SHIP_1_SHIP T1 JOIN SHIP_1_CAPTAIN T2 ON T1.SHIP_ID  =  T2.SHIP_ID WHERE T2.RANK  =  'Lieutenant'
